{"word":"ἀνδρικός","slug":"ἀνδρικός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνδρικός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀνήρ'><el>ἀνήρ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of</i> or <i>for a man, masculine, manly</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>virilis</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>ἀνδρ. ἱδρώς</el> the sweat <i>of manly toil</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-κῶς</el>, <i>like a man</i>, <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>-ώτερον</el>, <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>-ώτατα</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>composed of men</i>, <el>χορός</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}